==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exsufflation
<hw>Ex`suf*fla"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<ets>exsufflatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A blast from
beneath.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccles.)</fld> <def>A kind of exorcism by blowing
with the breath.</def> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A strongly forced expiration
of air from the lungs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exsufflicate</ent>⟦br⟧
